The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

NATION BRIEFS

 Hyderabad, June 6 (PTI): The city-based Emergency Management and Research Institute and the US-based Stanford School of Medicine today launched a two-year full-time residential postgraduate programme on emergency care. 

 ford physicians will train 150 paramedics and 30 advanced clinical educators. The programme, beginning from July 16, will cover clinical knowledge and skills in communication and education in emergency management. 

 New Delhi (PTI): A CBI team briefed law officials on Tuesday as part of the case being prepared for the prosecution in the extradition trial of Italian businessman Ottavio Quattrocchi, an accused in the Bofors scam. The trial begins on Friday in Misiones province in Argentina. 

 New Delhi (PTI): Two years after blasts rocked two cinema halls in the capital, police have traced the main conspirators members of pro-Khalistan outfit Babbar Khalsa International in Germany. A letter seeking information on them will be sent to Germany. 

 Kathmandu (PTI): Nepal police have arrested three Indians allegedly involved in trading banned shahtoosh shawls. They seized 19 pieces of the shawls from them. The accused were arrested after they sold a shawl to a police decoy for Rs 80,000. 

 Chamba (PTI): A man was killed and three persons were seriously injured when a huge rock slid down a mountain and hit them near Saach pass in Himachal Pradesh. Four others had a narrow escape. The pass has been closed for seven months and is yet to be officially reopened.

 Muzaffarnagar (PTI): A priest in a Jain shrine was found dead in the complex, police said on Wednesday. Ramkishen, 40, was found dead with his throat slit by devotees. Angry devotees staged a protest near the temple.




